column1: Use of a broken or weak cryptographic hashing algorithm on sensitive data
column2: Using broken or weak cryptographic hashing algorithms can compromise security.
column4: [["Sensitive data (password)"|"relative:///sqli/dao/user.py:40:30:40:37"]] is used in a hashing algorithm (MD5) that is insecure for password hashing, since it is not a computationally expensive hash function.
